@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - jms/Fleet
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Fleet spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetFleet;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListFleets using filters compartmentId,\ndisplayName, id;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateFleet when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteFleet with required via\nGetFleet or ListFleets to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetFleet or ListFleets\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, NEEDS_ATTENTION;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeFleetCompartment, UpdateFleet only\nfor mutable fields definedTags, description,\ndisplayName, freeformTags (+3 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=fleet action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=fleet action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=fleet action=DELETED when the matching\nfield-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet/ListFleets\nconfirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, NEEDS_ATTENTION\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: jms
slug: fleet
kind: Fleet
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet;
update=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet;
delete=GetWorkRequest -> GetFleet/ListFleets
confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, description,
displayName, freeformTags (+3 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_jms_fleets filters
compartmentId, displayName, id; exact
compartmentId plus displayName unique match in
ACTIVE, CREATING, UPDATING, or NEEDS_ATTENTION;
duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
NEEDS_ATTENTION as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a Fleet
body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected Fleet OCID
from work-request resources, and then rereads
GetFleet before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when
spec.compartmentId and spec.displayName are
present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or NEEDS_ATTENTION
summaries.
Only displayName, description, inventoryLog,
operationLog, isAdvancedFeaturesEnabled,
freeformTags, and definedTags reconcile in
place; operationLog updates only when both log
identifiers are supplied, compartmentId remains
replacement-only, and ChangeFleetCompartment
stays out of scope for the published runtime.
inventoryLog remains a required published spec
field because CreateFleet requires it from the
first published contract.
Required status projection keeps approximate
inventory counters, inventoryLog, operationLog,
export-setting state, and systemTags on the
published kind, and the runtime has no secret
side effects.
end note
@enduml
